Doctolib is facing new challenges thanks to our fast growth, and one of them is to establish Doctolib as a must have for all Healthcare Professionals in Europe. To accomplish that, we need to transform Doctolib approach to Lead Generation and become more online and inbound oriented. We have recently created the Global Lead Generation Team to pursue that objective.

Your missions
You will have an hybrid role within the company: you will be the analytics “master” for B2B lead generation, while helping Doctolib generating more leads and revenue. More concretely, your main objectives will be:

1) Understand the performance of all of our lead generation channels in order to increase the number of new inbound leads:
– Analyse and understand how we can get more leads through our Doctor Website, more particularly by i) increasing the traffic, and ii) optimizing the conversion rate;
– Coordinate the creation and maintenance of our reporting tools and monitoring dashboards on all of our channels with a data analyst
– Work closely with the Data team on providing us with proper tracking solutions, relevant and aggregated datasets, optimized dashboards, and leading more complex analyses.

Example analyses to expect: performance deepdive of all of our B2B online marketing campaigns, doctor website funnel analysis to make A/B testing / landing pages recommendations, attribution modeling etc.

2) Develop a perfect understanding of our sales cycles to identify inbound opportunities and improve the performance of our sales team:
– Extensively analyse our pipe management (funnels from lead to contract, nurturing cycles etc.), in collaboration with our Global Sales Strategy team, in order to generate new inbound leads and increase revenue;
– Build the relevant tools to monitor all of our inbound funnel: # leads, # meetings, conversion rate, MRR etc.;
– Define precise scenarii and build segmentation to launch automated nurturing campaigns using marketing automation tools (e.g. Pardot).

3) Generate leads from our existing customer base through network effect and upsell:
– Track, analyze and launch automated campaigns to generate new telehealth leads and contribute to new revenue streams;
– Track, analyze and enhance our ability to generate positive word-of-mouth and leads from doctors (patient referral network, doctor-to-doctor referrals, etc.);
– Scale our targeting methodologies for our future new products and markets.

Profil recherché
– You graduated from a Business School or Engineering School;
– You have at least 3 years of experience as a business or marketing analyst or/and a fast and successful track record in a B2B SaaS company;
– You’re comfortable writing basic SQL queries (incl. joins), and have already worked with Google Analytics;
– You have a strong business sense, with a growth hacking mindset;
– You have worked abroad or have an international experience;
– An experience with marketing automation tools (e.g. Hubspot, Pardot) is a plus;
– English is mandatory, French / Spanish / Italian are a plus.

